Information
------------------------------

Big Dreams Small Spaces: Series 2
Monty Don returns to help more amateur horticulturists transform their small or average-sized plots into something extraordinary.




4)  Oxford 
Monty helps Oxford neighbours Anne and Fliss, who want to combine the front gardens of their semi-detached homes into one single space filled with their favourite grasses and perennials. The gardening enthusiasts have some big ideas - but can they work together to achieve one goal? He also travels to Pewsey, where former Army officer Sally is converting a tarmac and rubble-covered area into a cosy, wildlife-friendly haven for her daughters. She wants it ready for summer, which doesn't give them a great deal of time - but she does have an army of friends willing to get involved.

5)  Worthing 
Worthing couple Emma and Josh want to transform their overgrown plot into a family garden for their son Noah, who has Down's syndrome. Monty Don helps them learn about different sensory plants - only for rain to jeopardise the project. In Hitchin, Aletheia is determined to create a neighbourhood vegetable patch and a trip to Cranbrook Community Garden in London proves it is possible - but can she persuade the other locals to join in?

6)  Teddington 
Teddington woman Jennifer enlists her sisters' help to create an Italian-themed garden in memory of their parents. However, growing citrus trees, olive trees and vines in a leafy London suburb is easier said than done. In Billericay, Karensa dreams of turning a messy strip of back garden into an Alice in Wonderland playground for her daughter, complete with chessboard patio, heart-shaped lawn and teapot water feature. The only problem is, she has little idea how to go about it. Can Monty bring her closer to her fantasy?
